    "narrative": "Our offensive ceiling today is anchored by **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (77.47) and **Mickey Moniak** (75.97), who represent our strongest plays. **Chisholm Jr.** benefits from a favorable matchup against Luis Severino, where his dynamic platoon edge and raw power profile overcome a marginal penalty for facing a high-efficiency catcher. Meanwhile, **Moniak** is a high-upside start due to the combined tailwinds of a hitter-friendly park and a significant platoon advantage against the struggling Cristian Javier. **James Wood** (73.87) also maintains elite status, bolstered by his prime spot in the leadoff hole and a favorable matchup that promises high-volume opportunities to accumulate counting stats.\n\nThe decision to bench **Alex Freeland** (44.72) was the most difficult call of the morning; while his BvP historicals against the opposing starter are stellar, his raw efficiency failed to crack the top-tier of our middle infield options. We are also wary of the risks surrounding **Zach McKinstry** (50.50); while the wind blowing out helps his profile, he remains a marginal play hampered by a low spot in the batting order and a matchup that minimizes his stolen base potential. We are keeping a close watch on **Vinnie Pasquantino** (46.57), whose value is currently suppressed by a severe negative platoon split, making him a candidate to be pulled if we need to pinch-hit for a higher-floor option later in the evening.",
